Is The Lash industry is Dead!

I’ve notice a huge turn over in true lash artist .
It seems the love for detailed picky perfectionist lash art has disappeared. 

Remember that lash service is not a cheap service. On average requires 2-3 hours per set. 
Understand that watering down your technique In order to fit more clients in the day eventually hurts your business operations. 

The reason it take at least two hours to complete a Full set is because no matter how skilled you are, Proper attachment and isolation can not be traded for speed. 

In order to keep your clients coming back there has to be consistency in your workmanship, qaulity in your retention, and styling. 

You should not sneak in premade fans without client consent. Some Premades feel different 😒 
Also Stop trading in 100% lash coverage for bigger lash fans bc As soon as one lash falls out the client has a huge hole . 

Understanding basic strategies & the benefits of offering quality products and service is the only way to have longevity in business .

Are you a Lazy Lash Artist still expecting full compensation for mediocre Lash sets ? What’s lacking in your career? Are you just not motivated ? 

Let’s talk about below !
#lashartist #lashartisttips

Labor of L🫶🏽ve

Lash Talk 🥱 
Why did you only take one lash course ?
Why did you stop learning ?
The lash artist that’s killing it booked & busy are the ones running after lash trainings and continue to invest by building on their knowledge & skills !

Here’s what I wanted to LAsh Talk about 🤐 the artistry of lashing takes time and there’s no way around it.
A fullset of eyelash extensions was never designed to be completed under 2 hours . 
Mainly because isolating the natural lash and applying the lash extensions with intentional placement takes time. Rushing will effect the lash retention . 

Because it takes so long you must invest into becoming better and better one lash training is not enough 2-3 lash training your getting to groove of things . If you’re seeking abundance and desire to make an ROI you have to perfect these skills. Clients prefer lash artist that are detail oriented ! 

I know mega volume was trending for sometime but I’m here to remind you that you’re leaving money on the table not servicing the natural clients. Classics, Wispy , eyeliner effect Russian Volume looks are styles I swear by. I think being able to create bespoke lash designs for each client eye and vibe is what makes a person a true artist . 

Tip: try 10mm CC curl on outer corners it will create the perfect lift . Dropping corners give me anxiety 🫣

Let me know if y’all actually read this bc 🫨

A huge part of this journey is trail and Error.
You can’t expect to win if you’re not willing to take some L’s .

The loses or lessons are there to teach you . You learn what working and what’s not. 
You have to atleast try ! 
Create a plan using what you have now 

For example: the pictures in this photo was taken with my iPhone 14 Pro & my Sony A6 camera. 
I’m no pro photographer but I know what looks I want to capture so I get it done! I have fun and it always turns out great .

I’ve only used the Sony A6 camera 4-5 times.
My point is 👆🏾 book that model and get the photos you need . 
Stop waiting for that green light and start doing ! Allow yourself I explore and build embrace the emotions of uncertainty and allow it to drive your creativity . 

Truth is Photo shoots are expensive but this shouldn’t stop you. 
For now adapt the mentality that nothing will get in the way of what needs to be done inorder to move the needle And execute .

That vision that keeps nudging you!
The one you keep ignoring!
the one the keeps poking at you but you’re procrastinating to bring it to life. Yes that’s the one do it 🤎 

Write the vision down and trust it 📹

Lashme Academy

{Purpose driven}

The importance of gaining the correct foundational lash skills and theory has a direct impact on your success. This is something I have always been a firm believer in, and for good reason. Taking as many courses and lash training as possible not only helps you hone your skills, but it also gives you the confidence needed to present as an lash expert. This is crucial in building the clientele and lash business of your dreams.
In addition to the technical aspects of lash training, it is also important to understand the theory behind how lashes work and how to apply them in a way that produces natural and beautiful results. This is something that can be easily overlooked, but it is essential for achieving the best possible outcomes for your clients.
I would love to hear from anyone planning on expanding their knowledge in 2024. Some of your goals or interests could be anything from taking further courses in lash technique and technology, to learning how to open your own lash studio. The possibilities are endless, and I encourage everyone to pursue their passions and dreams.

Comment below to share some of your goals or interests, and let me know what you think about the importance of gaining the correct foundational lash skills and theory. 👇🏾
